            "y": 0.4114011373578303,
            "w": 0.6334554625984252,
            "h": 0.4712239720034996
          },
          "text": "Entrepreneurs are those who believe they can achieve what others say is impossible, taking action to bring into existence what does not yet exist.For entrepreneurs, who are more familiar with hearing \"no\" than \"yes\" and more accustomed to rejection than approval, the nickname \"underdog\" suits them better than \"top dog.“Inspired by the term \"underdog,\" which refers to a team or player with low chances of winning in sports, underdogs was founded with the belief that even the smallest possibilities can spark social innovation and create transformative change in the world through business. It is a collective of underdog entrepreneurs determined to flip the script and build a better world.Underdogs is a specialized institution for entrepreneurship education, dedicated to discovering and nurturing social innovation entrepreneurs both in Korea and abroad. Since its establishment in 2015, it has fostered over 19,000 social innovation entrepreneurs.",
